This paper primarily focuses on improving the performance of object detection using RGB-D data, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) domains. The paper proposes a two-stage learning framework for property derivation and fusion, which involves deep learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the paper is also likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE).
